headline: Jabil Tariffs Test Supply Chain Resilience And Valuation Gap For Investors
summary: Jabil (NYSE:JBL) is being hit with a new 15% global tariff introduced by the Trump administration. The tariff targets cross border trade and is set to affect Jabil’s international supply chain operations. Investors are assessing how the new cost structure may influence Jabil’s margins, pricing, and customer relationships. Jabil enters this tariff shock with shares trading at $264.99 and a 5 year return of more than 5x. The stock is up 10.2% year to date and 71.3% over the past 12 months,...
